  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Combine the fractions on the left over a common denominator (x \u2212 3)(x + 2): 3(x + 2) + 4(x \u2212 3) = 3x + 6 + 4x \u2212 12 = 7x \u2212 6. So rx + t = 7x \u2212 6, giving r = 7 and t = \u22126. Thus rt = (7)(\u22126) = \u221242.</p><p>Choices B, C, and D result from misidentifying or omitting the sign of t.</p>",
